t is the time steps you want to predict for the corresponding split.\r\n\r\n> Would appreciate a PR!\r\n\r\nI could give this a shot. This would be my first significant PR in any open-source project but seems doable for me.\r\n\r\nP.S.\r\nHow would you foresee the appropriate way to compare models trained at differing temporal aggregates? Obviously any predictions made on the disaggregate models would have to be aggregated together in order to compare performances with the most aggregate model. Right now, I imagine it can be done by supplying a custom `scoring` method to `ForecastingGridSearchCV` or `ForecastingRandomizedSearchCV` in which the user has to figure out how to group and aggregate predictions together. It's a little weird though because that `scoring` method would have to access global variables. But to get around that, I think we could use [partial functions](https://docs.python.org/3/library/functools.html#functools.partial). \r\n\r\nCurious if you think that would be an appropriate way to handle that issue or if you have other ideas.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/comments/1308017075/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":1,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"GianlucaGuarroSonos","id":107063818,"node_id":"U_kgDOBmGqCg","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/107063818?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/GianlucaGuarroSonos","html_url":"https://github.com/GianlucaGuarroSonos","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GianlucaGuarroSonos/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GianlucaGuarroSonos/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GianlucaGuarroSonos/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GianlucaGuarroSonos/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GianlucaGuarroSonos/subscrip